An ugly by-product of Japanese legal discrimination in this regard. In fact, you may even be surprised at how quickly the topic of divorce is broached in Japanese society, even on TV. Most Japanese men overlook bullying women to stay in relations that have no hope of improving. Because of Japan’s historic emphasis on family and the long-standing taboo against divorce, many couples cherish the appearance of a happy family even when it no longer exists.

Japanese Women and Peace Calls by Disabled People

There is debate among Japanese and international organizations regarding the definition of disabled women. Some figures were taken from a series of surveys by the Japan Statistical Association [10] [25] [26] [27] survey years: , , and Many of the statistics regarding disabled women reported over the past few decades have been low because the concept and definition of disabilities varied over time. Defining the statuses and identifying the service needs of disabled women has been difficult in the past because there have been few data collected by government or non-governmental organizations.
